I’ve been using this Braun IPL since 4 weeks now and I’m quite pleased with the results! 

IPL stands for intense Pulsed light and it uses a broad spectrum light to permanently reduce hair growth at the root itself which is cost effective and super convenient!

It’s easy and safe to use at home, no need for clinic appointments! 

Over the period of these 4 weeks I’ve seen a significant reduction in my hair growth (I tested it on my legs, once a week).

If you like a lightweight non-sticky lip oil, this is your sign to try the Clinique Black Honey Lip & Cheek Oil ✨ it’s sheer but with the right amount of healthy colour, doesn’t feel sticky or gloopy and hydrates dry winter lips really well! 

On the cheeks — it gives a very soft wash of colour (may not be enough pigment to show up well on deeper skin tones) and the soft dewy shine is really pretty on the cheeks, especially for dry skin types! I love it more than the Black Honey gloss!

COSRX was one of the brands that introduced me to the power of Korean skincare and I still love it today!

🌟 The 6 Peptide Booster is one of the favorites at the moment, it addresses multiple skin concerns and leaves my skin super hydrated and glowing!

🌟 If you have oily or acne prone skin, combine the Peptide Booster with The Niacinamide 15 Serum in the same routine for effective anti-acne action.

🌟 If signs of aging like lines, wrinkles, loss of firmness are your concern, combine the Peptide Booster Serum with their Retinol 0.3 Cream for powerful anti-aging benefits.

🌟 Make sure you use sunscreen daily in the day, especially if you are using the Retinol. And you won’t find one better than the Ultra-Light Invisible Sunscreen which is lightweight, refreshing and gives ample protection!

All the products above are available at @yesstyle! @cosrx @cosrx_uk 
Code COSRXAN for 12% off on orders over $69!

#DermMicellarWater #PeptideSerum #AcneCareSolution #RetinolCream #WrinkleCare #AsianSunscreen #KoreanSunscreen #COSRX #yesstyle AD
